The paper discusses the implementation of deep learning models for mobile applications, specifically focusing on Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of deep learning models for mobile hardware, which falls under the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also mentions real-time image recognition and conversational systems, which are related to Multimedia (cs.MM) and Augmented Reality (cs.AR) sub-categories, respectively.
